.TH "dwc2_check_periodic_bandwidth" 9 "dwc2_check_periodic_bandwidth" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dwc2_check_periodic_bandwidth \- Checks that there is sufficient bandwidth for the specified QH in the periodic schedule
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dwc2_check_periodic_bandwidth
.BI "(struct dwc2_hsotg *hsotg "  ","
.BI "struct dwc2_qh *qh "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hsotg" 12
The HCD state structure for the DWC OTG controller
.IP "qh" 12
QH containing periodic bandwidth required
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful, negative error code otherwise
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For simplicity, this calculation assumes that all the transfers in the
periodic schedule may occur in the same (micro)frame
